# Africana Driver Connect Mobile — Cursor AI Rules

## Project Context
Multi-page UI project exported from UXMagic Copilot.
Each HTML page uses Tailwind CSS v4 (browser runtime) with an inline @theme block.

## File Structure
- Splash & Onboarding Forms.html
- Authentication.html
- Role Selection.html
- Verification Pending.html
- Driver Dashboard.html
- Owner Dashboard.html
- Client Booking.html
- Admin Control Center.html
- styles.css   (shared — :root theme vars + scoped page styles)
- script.js    (shared — utilities + per-page IIFE blocks)
- package.json
- .cursorrules
- README.md

## Key Rules
- The <style type="text/tailwindcss"> block in each HTML file defines the theme.
  DO NOT move it to styles.css — the Tailwind v4 browser runtime reads it inline.
- Page content is wrapped in <div data-page="..."> for CSS scoping.
- Use Tailwind utility classes (bg-background, text-foreground, etc.) for styling.
- Do not add inline style= attributes.
